---
import Document from '../../layouts/document.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import { frontmatter as indexFrontmatter } from '../../../../../docs/en/index.md';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n/translations.ts';

const t = useTranslations('en');
---

<Document title={t('index.title')}>
  <main>
    <Hero title={indexFrontmatter['title']} intro={indexFrontmatter['intro']}>
      <Fragment slot="footer">
        <a
          class="nl-button nl-button--primary"
          href="https://github.com/nl-design-system/editor"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <span class="nl-button__label">{t('index.cta.github')}</span>
        </a>
        <a
          class="nl-button nl-button--secondary"
          href="https://github.com/orgs/nl-design-system/projects/70/views/27"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <span class="nl-button__label">{t('index.cta.roadmap')}</span>
        </a>
      </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="badges">
        <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@nl-design-system-community/editor">
          <img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@nl-design-system-community/editor" alt="npm version" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/nl-design-system/editor">
          <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/github-repo-blue?logo=github" alt="GitHub repository" />
        </a>
      </Fragment>
    </Hero>

    <Section>
      <div class="clippy-index__preview-bar">
        <a class="nl-button nl-button--secondary" href="/preview">
          <span class="nl-button__label">Preview</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <clippy-editor id="clippy-editor-localhost">
        <div slot="value">
          <h1>NL Design System Editor heading 1</h1>
          <p>
            Among the cities that <strong>have</strong>
            <i>long</i> adorned the <strong><i>comital</i></strong> crown of Holland like so many precious gems, and whose
            power and wealth provided a firm support for the authority of the Count, Haarlem, as is well known, was one of
            the most important.
          </p>
          <h2>NL Design System Editor heading 2</h2>
          <p></p>
          <h4>That is not allowed</h4>
          <p>
            Built on the banks of a river of which it made use as
            <a href="https://example.com">two arms</a> to reach, on the one side, the Haarlemmermeer and the surrounding lands,
            and on the other the IJ, and through the IJ, the Zuiderzee, it had already early taken advantage of this favourable
            position to conduct a<a href="https://example.com"> </a>trade that, though seldom extending further than the
            regions surrounding those inland seas, nonetheless provided it with opportunity.
          </p>
          <table>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <th>Name</th>
                <th colspan="3">Description</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Row 1, cell 1</td>
                <td>Row 1, cell 2</td>
                <td>Row 1, cell 3</td>
                <td>Row 1, cell 4</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <dl>
            <dt>Foo</dt>
            <dd>The meaning of foo</dd>
            <dt>Bar</dt>
            <dd>The meaning of bar</dd>
          </dl>
          <h2>Images</h2>
          <img alt="Test size 800x400" src="https://placehold.co/800x400" />
          <h3>Correct list</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Test</li>
            <li>Test</li>
            <li>Test</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>Incorrect numbered list</h3>
          <p>1 - Test<br />2 - Test<br />3 - Test</p>
        </div>
      </clippy-editor>
    </Section>
  </main>
</Document>

<style>
  .clippy-index__preview-bar {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding-block-end: var(--basis-space-block-sm);
  }
</style>
